Annex 7 and Phoenix.4.14.4MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS FOR A TRAINEE MARINE ENGINEER (TME), GRADUATE MARINE ENGINEER(GME)Any TME (Trainee Marine Engineer)/ GME (graduate Marine Engineer) joining a vessel shall:· proficient in English· be a graduate in Mechanical Engineering (for GME).· have undergone approved pre-sea training· have undergone the medical examination as per Flag of the vessel and be found “Fit for Sea Service”.· Comply with the requirements of the applicable 'Training and Qualifications Matrix' in Annex 7 and Phoenix.It shall be the responsibility of the manning office to verify that the above qualification requirements are met before being appointed.4.15RECRUITMENT AND SELECTION PROCEDURES4.15.1CREW PLANNING AND ASSIGNMENTThe crew planner takes into consideration staff requirements on the basis of vacancies arising on a vessel due to:1) completion of contract/ Charterer’s requirements2) signing off due to medical grounds3) request for early relief4) termination of contract5) desertionOn the basis of the requirements, replacements will be recommended for each staff who is due to sign off.Prior recommending the staff, the following factors are to be taken into consideration1) Suitability for the type of vessel being nominated,2) Experience in that particular rank and compliance with Charterer’s manning requirements3) Past performance record from his personal data file4) Whether adequately certificated.5) Reference checks from previous employers when available are satisfactory.6) Identified Training needs have been completedPreference shall be given to existing staff in which case suitability for promotion and possibility of rotation on the same vessel or sametype of vessel shall be considered.The above process is documented in the Phoenix 'Crew Module'.Note:In case a crew member is being signed off without reliever due to sign off on medical grounds / compassionate grounds / terminationof contract or if the crew member has deserted the ship, the following formalities should be carried out as applicable.1. Inform vessel's flag state and local authorities in case of desertion.2. Inform the P & I club in case of medical sign off / desertion.3. Check if vessel is complying with minimum safe manning and obtaining dispensation if required.4. Inform charterers if vessel is in breach of their manning requirements and obtain their approval for vessel to continue short manned.5. Inform next of kin in case of desertion.4.15.2PROCEDURES FOR RECRUITING NEW STAFF
